<AbstractNarration>EEC-0002918&lt;br/&gt;Shoureshi&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;The goal of the Pserc Center at the Colorado School of Mines will be to integrate advances from power systems, control theory, artificial intelligence, diagnostics, new sensor-technologies, etc. to assist the electric utility industry in facing these new challenges.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;The research, which is complementary to those of the other Pserc sites, will focus on the following topics:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Development of Intelligent Substation; Advanced Power Generation Control with Integrated Economics, Variable Demands and Short-Term Load Forecast; Development of Advanced Sensors and Sensory Feedback Systems for Increased Reliability and Lower Maintenance Cost; Predictive Maintenance for Reduction of Operating Cost; Development of Remote Health Assessment Techniques T&amp;D; and EMAT Based Diagnostics of Overhead Transmission Lines.&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
